\textbf{\Large Introduction}

\begin{itemize}
\item Carbapenem-resistant Enterobacteriaceae (CRE) are a major hospital infection risk.
\item Agent-based models (ABM) simulate transmission dynamics in ICUs.
\item However, ABM simulations are computationally expensive.
\end{itemize}

\bigskip

\textbf{\Large ABM Model}

\begin{itemize}
\item Individual-level simulation of patient interactions
\item Transmission probability parameter $\beta_{ABM}$
\item Monthly incidence data generated
\end{itemize}

\bigskip

\textbf{\Large Motivation}

\begin{itemize}
\item Fast inference for transmission parameters
\item Build a surrogate model approximating ABM dynamics
\end{itemize}

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
% COLUMN 2
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

\column{0.33\textwidth}

\textbf{\Large Method: SMoRe ParS}

\begin{enumerate}
\item Run ABM simulations
\item Fit surrogate model
\item Map parameters between models
\end{enumerate}

\bigskip

\textbf{\Large Surrogate Model}

Example difference equation:

\[
I_{t+1} = I_t + \beta_{SM} S_t I_t
\]

\bigskip

\textbf{\Large Parameter Mapping}

Goal:

\[
\beta_{ABM} \rightarrow \beta_{SM}
\]

Estimated using

\begin{itemize}
\item Maximum Likelihood Estimation
\item Poisson likelihood
\item AIC / BIC model comparison
\end{itemize}

